cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CE, cs.IR, cs.DS

This paper focuses on predicting stock prices using deep learning models, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of sparse autoencoders and convolutional neural networks also suggests the category of computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV). The inclusion of macroeconomic variables in the feature set suggests the category of information retrieval (cs.IR) or data science (cs.DS). Finally, the use of LSTM for time series prediction suggests the category of computational engineering, finance, and science (cs.CE).
